Here are 10 words that meet the given criteria:

1. Rhinoceros - from Greek "rhino" meaning nose and "keras" meaning horn
2. Anomaly - from Greek "anomalos" meaning uneven or irregular
3. Archetype - from Greek "archetypon" meaning original pattern or model
4. Euphoria - from Greek "euphoros" meaning well-bearing
5. Gossamer - from Middle English "gossomer" meaning fine, filmy substance
6. Kowtow - from Mandarin "kòu tóu" meaning to knock one's head
7. Myriad - from Greek "myrias" meaning ten thousand
8. Ostracism - from Greek "ostrakon" meaning pottery shard (used in ancient Greece to vote for exile)
9. Quintessence - from Latin "quinta essentia" meaning fifth essence (believed to be the substance that makes up the stars)
10. Zeitgeist - from German "Zeit" meaning time and "Geist" meaning spirit, referring to the prevailing mood or spirit of a particular time period.
